---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import SEOHead from '../../components/SEOHead.astro';
import Navbar from '../../components/Navbar.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
---

<BaseLayout>
  <SEOHead slot="head" title="Tattoo Aftercare Automation — Complete Guide 2026 | InkFlow Blog" description="Automate tattoo aftercare with healing check-ins at day 3, 7, and 14. Increase healed photo submissions by 40%. Set it once, runs on autopilot." />
  <Navbar />

  <article class="pt-24 pb-16 sm:pt-32">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <p class="text-sm text-accent-400 mb-4">May 28, 2026</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold text-white sm:text-4xl">Tattoo Aftercare Automation: Complete Guide</h1>
      <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-gray-400">Automated aftercare check-ins increase healed photo submissions by 40% and review rates by 2x. Here's how to set it up and why it matters for your studio.</p>
    </div>
  </article>

  <section class="border-t border-ink-800/50 py-12">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 prose prose-invert">
      <h2>Why Aftercare Automation Matters</h2>
      <p>Most tattoo studios lose contact with clients after they walk out the door. No follow-up, no healed photos, no reviews. Automated aftercare changes that by sending the right message at the right time — day 3, day 7, and day 14 after each session.</p>
      <p>Studios using <a href="/features/aftercare" class="text-accent-400 hover:underline">InkFlow's aftercare automation</a> see 40% more healed photo submissions and 2x more reviews compared to manual follow-ups.</p>

      <h2>What an Automated Aftercare Sequence Looks Like</h2>

      <h3>Day 1: Aftercare Instructions</h3>
      <p>Sent immediately after the session. Includes washing instructions, product recommendations, and what to expect during healing. Clients appreciate having a clear reference.</p>

      <h3>Day 3: Healing Check-In</h3>
      <p>A quick text asking how the healing is going. Clients can reply with questions. This catches potential issues early and shows you care.</p>

      <h3>Day 7: Progress Check</h3>
      <p>Check in again. Ask if they need touch-up scheduling. Most clients forget to book touch-ups — this reminder alone increases return rates.</p>

      <h3>Day 14: Photo Request</h3>
      <p>Ask for a healed photo. This is your most powerful marketing asset. Real healed work builds trust with potential clients.</p>

      <h3>Day 21: Review Request</h3>
      <p>Send a review request with a direct link to your Google Business Profile or Yelp. Happy clients at this stage are most likely to leave a positive review.</p>

      <h2>Benefits of Automation</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Clients feel cared for — 35% higher retention with automated follow-ups</li>
        <li>More healed photos for your portfolio — no more chasing clients</li>
        <li>More reviews — automated requests at the right time get 2x more responses</li>
        <li>Saves 3+ hours per week on manual follow-up messages</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Get Started</h2>
      <p><a href="/features/aftercare" class="text-accent-400 hover:underline">InkFlow's aftercare automation</a> is included in the Pro plan. Set up your sequence once and it runs automatically after every appointment.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-12 text-center border-t border-ink-800/50">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white">Automate Your Aftercare</h2>
    <a href="https://app.ink-flows.com/register" class="mt-6 inline-block rounded-lg bg-accent-500 px-8 py-3.5 text-base font-semibold text-ink-950 hover:bg-accent-400 transition-all">Try InkFlow Free</a>
  </section>

  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>
